body:
Here is the sample example code from documentation:
```
module our (input clk);
  reg readme /*verilator public_flat_rd*/;
  initial $finish;
endmodule
```
If I use [standard attributes](https://link.springer.com/chapter/10.1007%2F978-1-4615-1713-9_27) like this:
```
module our (input clk);
  (* verilator public_flat_rd *)
  reg readme;
  initial $finish;
endmodule
```
It will raise an exception:
```%Error: ../sim_main.cpp:10: No handle found```

So here is the problem that:
the attributes of verilator is not a standard ieee implementation, which will cause verilog generator(like chisel) to implement a dedicated attribute implementation to verilator.

Hope verilator can implement a standard attributes spec.
